🗄 DATABASE CONNECTION SYSTEM
🔹 When User Adds Database (FIRST TIME)

Yes — you MUST analyze schema once and store it.

This is critical.

Schema Ingestion Process:

When DB is connected:

Query:

information_schema.tables

information_schema.columns

primary keys

foreign keys

data types

Store in your internal DB:

tables:

id

db_id

table_name

description (nullable)

row_count_estimate

columns:

id

table_id

column_name

data_type

is_nullable

is_primary_key

is_foreign_key

description (nullable)

Generate semantic summary using LLM:

Describe what each table likely represents.

Detect fact tables vs dimension tables.

Detect time columns.

Store that summary.

🧠 How Schema Should Be Used Later

DO NOT send full schema every query.

Instead:

Embed table + column descriptions.

When user asks question:

Embed user question.

Retrieve top relevant tables via vector search.

Send only those tables to LLM.

This:

Reduces tokens

Improves SQL accuracy

Prevents random joins

🔐 SQL GUARDRAILS

Never execute raw LLM SQL directly.

SQL Validation Rules

Allowed:

SELECT only

WITH (CTE)

GROUP BY

ORDER BY

LIMIT

Blocked:

DROP

DELETE

UPDATE

ALTER

INSERT

TRUNCATE

GRANT

REVOKE

Also enforce:

Automatic LIMIT 1000 (if none provided)

Query timeout (e.g., 5 seconds)

Read-only DB user

Use SQL parser library.
Never regex-only validation.

🧾 STRUCTURED OUTPUT CONTRACT (CRITICAL)

LLM must return ONLY JSON.

No text.

