🧠 CONVERSATION MEMORY SYSTEM

You need 2 layers of memory:

1️⃣ Short-Term Chat Memory

Per conversation store:

Last query

Last filters

Last date range

Last DB context

Example:

User:
“Show revenue in Bangalore”

User:
“Break that by sport”

Second query should reuse:

Same date range

Same city filter

Store conversation state as structured object:

{
"db": "sportomic",
"filters": {
"city": "Bangalore",
"date_range": "last_7_days"
},
"last_metric": "revenue"
}

Send this context in system prompt every turn.

2️⃣ Long-Term Memory

Store:

Saved reports

User preferred date range

Default DB

Do not send full history to LLM.
Summarize conversation context instead.

🧠 SYSTEM PROMPT DESIGN PRINCIPLES

Each mode gets separate system prompt.

System prompt must:

Instruct to output JSON only

Forbid explanation text

Forbid SQL mutations

Restrict to provided schema

Never hallucinate columns

Example instruction:

"You must only use provided tables and columns. If required column does not exist, return error JSON."

🧩 SCHEMA ANALYSIS BEST PRACTICE

Yes.

Do full schema ingestion ONCE when DB is added.

Store it.

Update manually if schema changes.

Do not re-fetch every query.

For large DB:

Cache schema in Redis

Use vector search to fetch relevant tables

This is scalable and clean.

